JOHANNESBURG - The Gupta brothers' nephew Varun is trying to leave South Africa despite a court order saying he can't. He has filed papers to have his bail conditions relaxed. He has been implicated in the misappropriation of funds for the Estina Dairy project and was released on R250,000 bail in February. READ: Gupta-linked associates in court for Vrede farm project Gupta apparently wants to leave the country on Thursday, saying he needs to attend a religious ceremony in India. The Daily Maverick website says his application will be heard on Monday. The nephew was CEO of Oakbay Resources until he resigned in April 2016. eNCA